d statements about the leader.\n\nThere were constant talks of hoping Labour loses key elections in order to instigating a coup and remove Corbyn as leader. There were statements expressing that Labour should on the losing side for the [[2016 United Kingdom local elections|2016 local elections]] and [[2016 United Kingdom European Union membership referendum|2016 European Union referendum]]. Furthermore, there is overwhelming evidence of the senior management obstructing party efforts to win the [[2017 United Kingdom general election]] in order to remove Corbyn. The management team co-ordinated in \"refusing to share basic information to LOTO during the election\", created a \"parallel general election campaign\" and boasted about \"hardly working\" during the campaign. There are marked statements about their dismay at Labour over-performing expectations during the campaign, and apparent disappointment with the increase in seats after the election.\n\n== Reaction ==\nMany MPs, party members and activists within the Labour Party expressed dismay at the contents of the report. Many Labour politicians across the party's spectrum spoke out against the emails and practices revealed in the report<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/AndyBurnhamGM/status/1249424188454076421?s=20|title=Yes, Ben, seems right to me. Always felt like the Party machine opposed my pro-public NHS & social care policies between 2010 & 2015. Not sure I had even-handed treatment from them in either the 2010 or 2015 leadership elections.https://twitter.com/_benbeach/status/1249419175895891980\u00a0\u2026|last=Burnham|first=Andy|date=2020-04-12|website=@AndyBurnhamGM|language=en|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/PaulaBarkerMP/status/1249662695466389504|title=Yesterday's leaked report laid bare the appalling antics of some at Labour HQ. We always knew they hated Jeremy, but I hope it is clear to those from other wings of our party that they deeply hated them too. (1